Arcelor, Brait and Medi-Clinic May Be Active in Early Johannesburg Trading

-- B y   S t e p h e n   G u n n i o n
-- 
2011-07-26T22:01:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-26/arcelor-brait-medi-clinic-south-african-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close.  The FTSE/JSE  Africa  All Share Index declined 197.11, or 0.6
percent, to 31,863.73 by the 5 p.m. close in Johannesburg.  ArcelorMittal South Africa Ltd. (ACL)  : Africa’s largest
steelmaker releases  first-half earnings . Shares in the company
fell 1.4 percent to 74.20 rand.  Brait SA (BAT)  : South Africa’s largest private equity
company holds its annual general meeting. The stock rose 0.1
percent to 17.86 rand.  Chrometco Ltd. (CMO)  : The chrome development company
holds a general meeting of shareholders. The shares slumped 8.8
percent to 31 cents.  Medi-Clinic Corp. (MDC SJ): South Africa’s second-largest
publicly traded private hospital holds its annual general
meeting. Shares of the company rose 0.1 percent to 32.22 rand.  Nampak Ltd. (NPK)  : The packaging company holds its
annual general meeting. The stock declined 0.2 percent to 22.45
rand.  Optimum Coal Holdings (OPT)  Ltd: The coal miner holds a
general meeting of shareholders. Shares in the company fell 2
percent to 24.50 rand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Gunnion in Johannesburg at 
 sgunnion@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
